This paper presents a learning-based mapless motion planner for mobile robots using deep reinforcement learning. The focus is on the navigation of mobile ground robots with a laser range sensor, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses deep learning techniques for training the motion planner, which suggests the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of image processing techniques for obstacle detection, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the trained planner in real-world environments, which suggests the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
